-- Hungary’s MVM Ovit Plans $13 Million Bio Mass Plant in Bosnia
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-12-03T13:55:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-03/hungary-s-mvm-ovit-plans-13-million-bio-mass-plant-in-bosnia.html
MVM Ovit Zrt, a unit of  Hungary ’s
state-owned power company Magyar Villamos Muvek Zrt., plans to
build a heating plant in northwestern Bosnia-Herzegovina, local
authorities said.  The biomass-fueled plant in Bosanska Krupa, whose
construction may begin in 2014, would cost about 10 million
euros ($13 million) and provide heat for the whole municipality
of more than 50,000 people, the local government said on its
 website , following a visit by MVM officials.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
